<br>
My first time in fear was last Wednesday before the thurs patch.  Zoned in with a SoE and Aego but otherwise completely nakid (left an already-rezzed corpse in Nexus to be rezzed out at the end).  Made it all the way to the N.wall, just above the wall of fire, without taking damage from agro - fear mobs don't run any faster than maybe t-boots.  Did my /q out at the wall then re-logged to make sure I was in a non-agro area, said 'hello' to the two druid scouts that were checking out pops and camped.<br>
<br>
Logged in the next day after the patch, Cazic was up.  Took 1.5hrs to get into good position for speaking the key phrase, then another 35min for him to be in position to do the turn in's.  Still had nearly 20min on rez timer so just asked a cleric in the Nexus to click that corpse instead of worrying about using a port potion - never even got agro for this whole part =)<br>
<br>
It IS possible, just really, REALLY stupid!<br>
<br>
